The paper discusses a novel data structure for compiling weighted graphical models, which is a topic that falls under the areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of AND/OR search spaces and Ordered Binary Decision Diagrams (OBDD) also suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the discussion of Variable Elimination and APPLY algorithms suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the potential application of the AOMDD data structure to systems and control (cs.SY) is briefly mentioned in the abstract.
